cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.PL, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new representation language and algorithms for multi-agent epistemic planning, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper makes use of a normal form called alternating cover disjunctive formulas (ACDFs) to support efficient reasoning in the multi-agent KD45 logic.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is another likely category as the paper focuses on multi-agent epistemic planning, which is a subfield of MAS.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new representation language for planning.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is an unlikely category as the paper does not seem to be related to digital libraries.
